# Responsive Portfolio Website

This project is a responsive portfolio website built using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It was developed as a part of the Oasis Infobyte Internship, specifically under the Web Development section Level 2.

## Table of Contents

- [Description](#description)
- [Features](#features)
- [Usage](#usage)
- [Contributing](#contributing)

## Description

The Responsive Portfolio Website is a showcase of web development skills, demonstrating proficiency in front-end technologies such as HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. It serves as a platform to display projects, skills, and experiences in a visually appealing and accessible manner.

## Features

- Responsive design: The portfolio website is designed to be compatible with various screen sizes, ensuring optimal viewing experience across devices, including desktops, tablets, and mobile phones.
- Home page: The home page introduces the visitor to the portfolio and provides navigation to different sections.
- About section: This section presents information about the developer, including their background, skills, and interests.
- Portfolio section: Visitors can view a collection of projects completed by the developer, including descriptions and links to project repositories or live demos.
- Contact section: A contact form or contact information is provided to allow visitors to get in touch with the developer.
- Navigation menu: Users can easily navigate through different sections of the portfolio website using an interactive navigation menu.
- Smooth scrolling: JavaScript is used to implement smooth scrolling behavior when navigating through sections of the website.
- Dynamic content: JavaScript may be used to dynamically load content or enhance interactivity on the website.

## Usage

Once the portfolio website is open in your web browser, you can navigate through different sections to explore the developer's profile, view projects, and find contact information. The website is designed to be intuitive and user-friendly, providing a seamless browsing experience.

## Contributing

Contributions to the Responsive Portfolio Website project are welcome! If you'd like to contribute, please follow these steps:

1. Fork the repository.
2. Create a new branch (`git checkout -b feature/fooBar`).
3. Make your changes.
4. Commit your changes (`git commit -am 'Add some fooBar'`).
5. Push to the branch (`git push origin feature/fooBar`).
6. Create a new Pull Request.
